text: "It is surely the pursuit of peace that is most needed in this world so full of strife." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "As members of Congress reflect on their pending decision, I urge them to set aside political considerations.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "As Americans, we should be proud of this achievement." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "Now we have before us a solution that prevents Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon without resorting to war." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "President Kennedy warned Americans not to see conflict as inevitable. It is time to apply such wisdom.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "I have repeatedly challenged anyone opposed to this deal to put forward a better, plausible alternative." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "When we carefully examine the arguments against this deal, none of them stand up to scrutiny.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "If Iran violates this deal, we will have ample opportunity to respond." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "Worry less about being labeled weak. Worry more about getting it right.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "How can we in good conscience justify war before we have tested a diplomatic agreement that achieves our objectives?" —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: “The choice we face is ultimately between diplomacy or some sort of war.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: “Walk away from this agreement and you will get a better deal—for Iran.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: “Those who say we can walk away from this deal and maintain sanctions are selling a fantasy.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "We will continue to have sanctions in place on Iran's support for terrorism and violation of human rights."—President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: “There is no scenario where sanctions relief turns Iran into the region's dominate power.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: “An argument against sanctions relief is effectively an argument against any diplomatic solution.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "Without this deal, the scenarios that critics warn about happening in 15 years could happen six months from now." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "The bottom line is, if Iran cheats, we can catch them—and we will." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: “This deal is not just the best choice among alternatives—this is the strongest non-proliferation agreement ever.” —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: “If Iran violates the agreement over the next decade all of the sanctions can snap back in to place.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "Iran has powerful incentives to keep its commitments." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "This deal shuts off the type of covert program Iran has pursued in the past.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "In July, we reached a comprehensive plan of action that meets our objectives." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "What was once proclaimed as a historic mistake is now held up as a success." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: “The progress of Iran's nuclear program was halted for the first time in a decade.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "It was diplomacy that ratcheted up the pressure on Iran." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "Winning this global buy-in was not easy. I know. I was there." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "What made our new approach more effective was our ability to draw upon new U.N. Security Council resolutions." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: “It was our very willingness to negotiate that helped America rally the world to our cause.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "I have also made clear my preference for a peaceful diplomatic resolution of the issue." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "Even before taking office, I made clear that Iran would not be allowed to acquire a nuclear weapon on my watch." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "The question then is not whether to prevent Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon, but how." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: "Now more than ever, we need clear thinking in our foreign policy." —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

text: “More than a decade later, we still live with the consequences of the decision to invade Iraq.” —President Obama #IranDeal
name: Barack Obama

name: Barack Obama

text: "Justice and redemption go hand in hand." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "Justice is living up to the common creed that I am my brother's keeper and I am my sister's keeper." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "Justice is making sure that every young person knows that they are special and their lives matter." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "Justice is not only the absence of oppression—it is the presence of opportunity." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "Let's reward prisoners with reduced sentences if they complete programs that make them less likely to repeat an offense." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "I've asked my Attorney General to start a review of the overuse of solitary confinement in our federal prisons." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "We should not tolerate conditions in prison that have no place in any civilized country." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

name: Barack Obama

text: "We should pass a sentencing reform bill through congress this year." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "For nonviolent drug crimes, we need to lower long mandatory minimum sentences—or get rid of them entirely." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "Don't just tag them as future criminals. Reach out to them as future citizens." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

name: Barack Obama

text: "We gotta make sure boys and girls in those communities are loved and cherished and nurtured and invested in." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "What doesn't make sense is treating entire neighborhoods as danger zones." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "We recognize that every child deserves opportunity. Not just some. Not just our own." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "This is a cause that is bringing people in both houses of Congress together." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

text: "Mass incarceration makes our country worse off—and we need to do something about it." —President Obama
name: Barack Obama

name: Barack Obama

text: "Our nation is being robbed of men and women who could be workers and taxpayers." —President Obama
